Bomb Blast Kills 40 in Eastern Afghan City: Report 
At least 40 people were killed and 150 others injured today in a bomb
blast in the eastern Afghan city of Jalalabad, according to reports
reaching here.
The explosion wrecked the building of the city's police headquarters,
the report said.
Jalalabad was seized by the Afghan Islamic militia Taliban before its
capture of the Afghan capital Kabul in September last year.
It is said that the police complex included a holding area for
prisoners.
The report said two hospitals in Jalalabad were crowded with the
injured following the blast.
